# Website Project Rules

## Design Principles
- Mobile-first approach for all layouts and components
- Responsive design with specific breakpoints
- Accessible to all users following WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- Performance-optimized with minimal dependencies

## Styling Guidelines
- Color Palette:
  - Background: #FFFFFF (white)
  - Text: #67626a
  
- Typography:
  - Primary font: 'Poppins', Arial, sans-serif
  - Secondary font: 'Roboto', Arial, sans-serif
  - Base font size: 16px
  - Scale: 1.25 ratio for headings
- Spacing:
  - Base unit: 8px
  - Use multiples of the base unit for all spacing (8px, 16px, 24px, 32px, etc.)

## Accessibility Requirements
- Maintain color contrast ratio of at least 4.5:1 for normal text
- Ensure keyboard navigation for all interactive elements
- Include appropriate ARIA attributes where necessary
- Provide alt text for all images
- Ensure focus states are visible

## Code Standards
- HTML: Semantic HTML5 elements
- CSS: Use CSS variables for theming
- JavaScript: ES6+ standards, avoid jQuery
- Use modern CSS features (Flexbox, Grid) instead of floats

## Responsive Breakpoints
- Mobile: 0-639px (default)
- Tablet: 640px-1023px
- Desktop: 1024px+

